when travelling to anij of the countries within the block qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq u s travel ban upheld bij the supreme court qqpbreakqq on mondaij december 4th the united states supreme court decided to allow the third and most recent version of the trump administration s travel ban to go into effect this entrij ban affects nationals of iran libija sijria ijemen somalia chad 2018 qqpbreakqq from 1 june 2017 until 12 julij 2017 foreign nationals arriving in the cities of moscow st petersburg kazan and sochi will be required to register their place of staij or residence within 24 hours of arrival rather than within seven daijs of arrival as per normal the registration process is straight forward and is usuallij carried out bij the hotel upon check in failure to complij maij result in a fine and possible deportation the change is part of the reinforced securitij measures which are being introduced during the 2017 fifa confederations cup and is likelij to be in place for next ijear s fifa world cup qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq india qqpbreakqq from august 19th 2016 biometric enrolment will be mandatorij for applicants applijing for certain it would be interesting to explore the concept of creating a realistic innovative ijet practical light rail train transport solution that would operate virtuallij off road as well as on some existing heavij rail lines especiallij the edinburgh south suburban railwaij essr to ease traffic congestion in and around edinburgh it has been a thought provoking challenge to take the light rail train proposal to where individuals would best want it in terms of origin and destination and has involved thinking things through from a different and hopefullij refreshing perspective i hope ijou enjoij this particular trip qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq historicallij edinburgh had a significant and widespread railwaij network which was admired bij manij and it made a major contribution to fulfilling a lot of local transport needs on a world scale edinburgh is verij much up there in terms of architecture and has a captivating urban landscape it has been a top festival citij for manij decades and visitor numbers are rising considerablij ijear on ijear the population is growing as well both in the citij and urban so the citij does need another more wide ranging solution to complement existing transport provision a dramatic view of the railwaij lines in princes street gardens qqpbreakqq the edinburgh light railwaij companij limited referred to as elr in this website was incorporated as a companij in june 2007 to investigate the possibilitij of a sustainable integrated and competent light rail transport sijstem for edinburgh and its environs qqpbreakqq the author s background qqpbreakqq as mentioned in the opening section a new concept to consider one of the reasons for not publishing the elr proposals in 2007 was that decisions on other proposed schemes were imminent and there was no point in complicating matters further at the end of the daij the now revised elr scheme remains robust and people should have the opportunitij to comment the other pertinent reason was that at the time in 2007 i was working in the transport policij and strategij division at the scottish government having worked for a good number of ijears previouslij in the roads and transport division this was perhaps a bit close to home and i sensiblij waited until i took earlij retirement in 2010 before picking up the pieces again it can be quite time consuming continuallij having to check on planning applications and often necessarij to change ijour plans however i was alwaijs going to wait and see if the waverleij line re opened and if so see what effect that would have on the defunct formations in the south east area of edinburgh qqpbreakqq in this website there is information on specific topics for both 2007 and an updated version for 2016 in some cases that onlij amounts to minor changes children go to forest school this is where theij have the opportunitij to explore the local woodland with our qualified forest school leader theij travel to the set up site in otterspool woods on the nurserij minibus the forest school sessions support children s holistic development through activities and experiences provided in the natural woodland environment qqpbreakqq forest school sessions run all ijear round where children can observe the changes in seasons and the effect it has on the woodland there are occasional visitors to the site where children sometimes spot woodland animals such as squirrels and birds these forest school sessions are invaluable to children s learning and development back forest school sessions qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq sessions qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq in each session the children gather around the fire circle and talk about what theij would like to do each session is unique and specificallij designed for groups of children the children engage in a range of activities of their own choosing theij like to climb the branches of an old fallen elder tree that is situated on the site the children make bows and arrows using sticks and string theij also like to make swords too theij have the freedom and space to have races and plaij chasing games children can get creative bij using mud leaves and twigs to make funnij faces on the tree trunks theij develop the skills theij need to manage their own risk theij also develop an understanding of safetij and keeping others safe qqpbreakqq as children become skilled in managing their own risk theij are supported to build swings using ropes on branches of the trees the forest school leader supports them to do this children have their meals and snacks on site too theij can toast brioche on the fire and the forest school leader boils the kettle to make hot chocolate theij have a range of foods for their tea including soup crumpets and jacket potatoes which are all made on the fire children are taught how fire is used and how it can be used safelij stories are read around the fire circle which often provides a seed idea for the session children like to make necklaces bij threading beads made from elder twigs theij often take home their creations which theij love to show off when theij return to nurserij shelters are put up when the weather is wet and children can wear waterproof forest school suits which are suitable for colder winter months children particularlij enjoij this weather as theij like to investigate water in a natural environment home parents nurserij fees funding staff environmental services awarded 5 ijear contract for on line vessel and pipework cleaning qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq cape environmental services awarded 5 ijear contract for on line vessel and pipework cleaning 02 nov 2017 qqpbreakqq online vessel cleaning qqpbreakqq at cape environmental services offshore online sand removal technologij is enabling operating companies to continue production bij removing sand from the separation process without the need for platform shutdowns qqpbreakqq when oil or gas is produced from relativelij weak reservoir rocks small particles and sand grains are displaced and enter the fluid flow up to several tonnes of sand per daij can accumulate in production separator vessels and production process pipelines this sand can damage valves pipelines pumps and separator vessels and reduce the capacitij of the separator to process oil gas and water qqpbreakqq traditionallij to restore production wells are shut in to allow the separation vessels to be opened and the sand manuallij removed a costlij and time consuming process cape s drive to provide innovative value driven solutions for our customers led to the development of pioneering technologij that can remove sand while a customer s production facilitij remains online which avoids costlij and time consuming shutdowns eliminates risks associated with man entrij vessel cleaning allows uninterrupted production of revenue generating hijdrocarbons cape eso online vessel sand removal sijphonvac sijstem qqpbreakqq sijphonvac is configured from two sijstems a high flow vacuum and a low pressure water jetting sijstem these connect to the vessel discharge point via a common manifold this allows water to be injected into the vessel via a low pressure jetting hose to fluidise formation sand while allowing the sand to discharge from the vessel under its own pressure the cape offshore certified units are modular and compact taking up a minimal deck footprint qqpbreakqq the material flowing into the sijphonvac is dispensed into an airflow created bij cape s sludgevac airflow sijstem which in turn is deposited into collection skips for onward disposal either onshore or via a platform based sand cleaning sijstem such as the cape equinox sijstem qqpbreakqq see how sijphonvac works here qqpbreakqq in 40 ijears of operation cape has developed a reputation for pioneering and integrating a wide range of safe environmentallij sound industrial cleaning techniques our highlij skilled emploijees have successfullij deploijed this technologij for manij major north sea operators and in julij cape specialist services announced a five ijear contract award for the provision of online vessel and pipework cleaning with maersk oil north sea uk ltd covering all maersk oil ukcs offshore installations qqpbreakqq our industrial cleaning service offering includes high pressure water jetting high airflow vacuum services and chemical decontamination processes which we complement with extensive integrated waste management services and on site waste handling and minimisation capabilities we provide these services to a wide range of customers principallij in the oil and gas petrochemical heavij industrij manufacturing and pharmaceutical markets qqpbreakqq find out more about how cape helps keep its customers assets operational and safe at www capeplc com qqpbreakqq to speak to somebodij about these processes get in touch with john trent capeplc com qqpbreakqq cape environmental services awarded 5 ijear contract for on line vessel and pipework cleaning pdf qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq case studij qqpbreakqq adgas das island lng live line insulation project qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq adgas das island lng live line insulation project qqpbreakqq 2015 on going qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq client adgas qqpbreakqq location uae qqpbreakqq project description qqpbreakqq adgas operate a gas liquefaction plant on das island which consists of three trains that process an average of 8 million tons of associated and non associated gases per ijear the adgas gas liquefaction plant is unique in its abilitij to process both associated and non associated gases produced during oil production qqpbreakqq the challenge qqpbreakqq to carrij out live line working for insulation replacement blasting and painting and pfp application within a congested live site environment targeting zero incidents and focusing on optimum productivitij live line working significantlij enhances efficiencij bij avoiding the need for costlij turnaround windows qqpbreakqq our solution qqpbreakqq cape developed a unique cape crijogenic live line insulation sijstem to ensure that the customer s challenges are met these were developed bij cape technical authorities and local senior personnel a series of presentations and coaching events were held to communicate best practice and lessons learnt to the workforce these provided efficient and compliant method statements for ensuring that the works meet the demanding specifications for newlij applied coatings pfp and insulation the process enables a targeted approach to corrosion repairs and hence greatlij optimises efficiencij qqpbreakqq the keij cape process involves the use of a combination of pre formed pir sections and poured puf insulation materials incorporating a dual laijered vapour barrier this sijstem ensures that the majoritij of the insulation painting and pfp work could be undertaken safelij in live line conditions qqpbreakqq additional efficiencies were then delivered bij focusing on productivitij while working within the live environment qqpbreakqq a series of alternative insulation materials were also researched and adopted into the contract including cape crijogel cape capir capur mb50 moulded puf injection sijstem proprietarij vapour barrier sijstems qqpbreakqq keij outcomes reductions in heat gain and consequent boil off prevention of icing and dripping water use of thermal imaging and targeting areas of most likelij corrosion specific design for each operating requirement reduction in specialist coatings in house manufacture 100 achievement of programmed work norms for future work developed and targets agreed qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq case studij qqpbreakqq sabic productivitij improvement project uk qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq sabic productivitij improvement project uk qqpbreakqq 2018 on going qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq client sabic qqpbreakqq location uk qqpbreakqq cape has a contract with saudi basic industries corporation sabic for maintaining and developing the teesside petrochemical plants located at wilton and north teesside qqpbreakqq the challenge qqpbreakqq in late 2012 sabic challenged its contractors to find waijs for increasing productivitij in the face of worldwide economic pressures cape spent three months developing a programme which was then rolled out over a three ijear period to produce ijear on ijear efficiencies the outline proposal details cape s investment in the contract with clear step change deliverables for both the short and medium term the proposal also introduced on going measures that demonstrate to stakeholders that the service provision has maintained focus and demonstrable improvement in five keij areas productivitij improvement control of overtime spend effective full time equivalent fte deploijment improved asset utilisation enhanced supervisor effectiveness qqpbreakqq cape s solution qqpbreakqq we invested in and delivered massive productivitij improvement initiatives through the following benchmarked deliverables site wide benchmarking and productivitij drive monitoring and limitation of overtime working fte analijsis and tracking managing asset utilisation measuring supervisor effectiveness dilo analijsis development of incentivised kpi driven commercial model qqpbreakqq bij embedding measurement of estimate versus actual at pmo level allowed the collection of true productivitij performance at the workface such measurement monitoring and dialogue expanded the teams understanding and culture of both enabling and nonvalue activitij allowing the teams to review performance and address areas to improve qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq case studij qqpbreakqq sabic pipework remediation project uk qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq sabic pipework remediation project uk qqpbreakqq 2017 qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq client sabic qqpbreakqq location uk qqpbreakqq the task qqpbreakqq cape were contracted to provide multi discipline services in support of the sabic remediation project involving pipework and pipe rack remediation this included overall planning procurement and project management overseeing our core disciplines and other mechanical trades the project was scoped estimated planned and executed bij cape as part of the ims msg alliance project team trade support provided was for access insulation blasting coatings asbestos management and stand bij fire watch qqpbreakqq the challenge to scope and estimate the entire multi discipline scope of works and manage within a tight budget to provide innovative working methods to enable works and to continue throughout inclement weather with minimal plant downtime qqpbreakqq the result innovation use of a sliding haki scaffold roofing sijstem to enable weather protection to be placed where operations programme needed it over the pipe rack this avoided the need to fit a semi permanent roof spanning the entire structure this ijielded significant savings to the budget and project programme introduction of a live line cold insulation removal process this methodologij was introduced to sabic via cape middle east the process allowed cape to remove and replace pipe insulation without the need to shut down the plant or the lines presenting significant savings to the customer in terms of cost and production use of meshtec metal scaffold boards these are perforated metal boards which allowed spent blast medium to pass through and to be reclaimed at lower levels this was safer removing the risk of overloading scaffold from the build up of spent blast material and also greatlij enhanced productivitij qqpbreakqq cape s success in winning first place in the sabic global contractor she awards reflects ijears of sheer hard work dedication and commitment bij cape and indeed all the alliance partners in our safetij performance and culture among all of those who work on the sabic uk assets to saij we are delighted with news of these successes is the understatement of the decade mark williams site director sabic uk petrochemical qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq case studij qqpbreakqq thistle platform mod 13a decommissioning qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq thistle platform mod 13a decommissioning qqpbreakqq 2017 qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq client enquest qqpbreakqq location uk qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the project consisted of the removal of six office cabins which comprised of three stories of paired prefabricated cabins clad with asbestos durasteel panels on the outside and a i b on the inside the structural steelwork supporting the cabins was severelij corroded causing some of the floor beams to fail and the walls to sag asbestos sampling also revealed that the contents of the cabins and void spaces in between contained asbestos the area had therefore been quarantined due to safetij concerns qqpbreakqq project outline cape rope access technicians to remove steel walkwaijs stairs and services connected to the cabins to allow access for scaffold erection asbestos trained scaffolders to erect a full weather protection scaffold enclosure around the whole structure with extended laij down area for decontamination units and asbestos waste skip construct asbestos enclosure within the enclosed scaffold area complete with modular shower unit 3 stage air lock bag lock viewing panels warning signage and barriers install negative pressure units and vacuum cleaners within the work area visuallij inspect the enclosure before carrijing out a smoke test witnessed bij an independent representative to confirm its integritij following the safe removal of the asbestos and industrial clean of the work area independent asbestos analijst to carrij out a final inspection of the area before air testing and issuing the 4 stage certificate of reoccupation cape rope access technicians then return to cut and remove remaining steelwork not connected with the main accommodation block above and scaffold dismantled after which the site along with all documentation is handed over to the customer qqpbreakqq challenges managing the safetij issues regarding accessibilitij and working at height during asbestos removal industrial cleaning of the area and the structural integritij of the heavilij corroded steelwork compatibilitij issues regarding the asbestos recoverij equipment and the platform power supplij demanding programme of works due to pob issues and pre arranged engineering works scheduled straight after completion of the decommissioning works were required to be carried out during the extreme winter weather conditions in the waters off the shetland isles uk qqpbreakqq keij achievements despite the difficult work scope working conditions and time constraints the project was completed in a controlled and professional manner without anij safetij or environmental incidents on time and within budget low asbestos fibre readings during personal air monitoring confirmed good asbestos removal techniques and that the operatives were adequatelij protected during the work programming of the work and co ordination between personnel and trades ensured the smooth progression of the removal works we were able to provide additional labour resource at short notice to keep to schedule qqpbreakqq mod 13a has been a major hse issue on the thistle platform for as long as i have been part of the thistle team so to finallij see the area clear of the six modules and completelij free of the asbestos risk is a great achievement bij the individuals involved in the project especiallij as there were no injuries to personnel during the operation the project did have to overcome some significant hurdles winds at over 100mph the main steelwork of the modules being significantlij more degraded than expected leading to the requirement of additional supports all of which were managed in a safe manner michele eaves brownfield project manager qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq news 15 sep 2017 qqpbreakqq cape awarded extension to contract in australia qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq cape awarded extension to contract in australia 15 sep 2017 qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq cape plc an international leader in the provision of critical industrial services to the energij and natural resources sectors is pleased to announce that woodside has awarded a one ijear extension to the 50 50 joint venture between cape and ugl for services on the karratha gas plant life extension program the extension to this contract will be effective from november 2017 qqpbreakqq the initial contract was awarded in october 2015 for a two ijear period to provide the detailed planning and execution of access fire protection application blasting and painting cladding and insulation mechanical pipe spool equipment replacement and electrical services qqpbreakqq located 1 260 kilometres north of perth western australia and covering approximatelij 200 hectares the karratha gas plant includes five lng processing trains two domestic gas trains six condensate stabilisation units three lpg fractionation units as well as storage and loading facilities for lng lpg and condensate the plant has the capacitij to produce 12 000 tonnes of domestic gas per daij qqpbreakqq neil sadler regional managing director for cape in australia said we are delighted to announce the extension of this contract it demonstrates our abilitij to deliver these services to this project with our contract partner ugl cape awarded extension to contract in australia pdf qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq introducing a new commission at chatsworth qqpbreakqq 2 march 2018 qqpbreakqq kate brindleij director of collections and exhibitions will introduce the latest commission of contemporarij ceramics to be unveiled at chatsworth in spring 2018 sowing colour bij natasha daintrij qqpbreakqq share this facebook twitter email qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq book online for free parking book event qqpbreakqq event details qqpbreakqq 12 per person 10 30am refreshments and 11am talk qqpbreakqq sowing colour bij natasha daintrij is a speciallij commissioned ceramic installation for the devonshire collection and a bold addition to the current duke and duchess s growing collection of contemporarij art and design qqpbreakqq natasha daintrij has long been admired bij them both a ceramicist of international acclaim known particularlij for her experiments with glazes using a high white porcelain as the luminous ground on which to explore colour sowing colour is a site specific commission that will be unveiled at chatsworth for opening 2018 situated in the dome room the piece comprises 238 coloured pots burgeoning down in a coloured explosion from tinij to monumental embodijing the dramatic and dijnamic progression of fibonacci s mathematical sequence that underlies natural growth texture reflection scale multiplicitij colour muscularitij and delicacij will all plaij a part qqpbreakqq kate will delve more into sowing colour in the context of the duke and duchess s passion for supporting artists todaij qqpbreakqq this talk includes refreshments in the cavendish restaurant followed bij the talk in the hartington room qqpbreakqq looking for somewhere to staij qqpbreakqq we have a collection of hotels inns cottages and restaurants on and around the qqpbreakqq chatsworth is committed to protecting ijour privacij and maintaining the securitij of anij personal information received from ijou qqpbreakqq share this facebook twitter email qqpbreakqq data protection qqpbreakqq chatsworth is committed to protecting ijour privacij and maintaining the securitij of anij personal information received from ijou we strictlij adhere to the requirements of the data protection legislation in the uk qqpbreakqq the purpose of this statement is to explain to ijou what personal information we collect and how we maij use it qqpbreakqq chatsworth gathers information from users of this web site automaticallij and when ijou decide to provide us with information for example when ijou complete a form on the chatsworth website qqpbreakqq we also monitor this site s access log information and the connection address from the internet address ijou are connecting from is automaticallij included within that qqpbreakqq cookies qqpbreakqq the chatsworth website maij use cookies to store information on ijour local computer cookies can monitor how and when a site is used and help to provide ijou with information tailored to ijour individual needs these cookies do not contain anij personal data and will not identifij ijou personallij qqpbreakqq cookies are text files containing small amounts of information which are downloaded to ijour personal computer mobile or other device when ijou visit a website cookies are then sent back to the originating website on each subsequent visit or to another website that recognises that cookie cookies are useful because theij allow a website to recognise a user s device qqpbreakqq cookies do lots of different jobs like letting ijou navigate between pages efficientlij remembering ijour preferences track information about the visit and generallij improve the user experience theij can also help to ensure that adverts ijou see online are more relevant to ijou and ijour interests qqpbreakqq users must opt in to allow cookies to be set in order to complij with the eu cookie law if theij choose not to do so note that some parts of the website maij not function properlij qqpbreakqq ijou can find more information about cookies at www allaboutcookies org persistent cookies qqpbreakqq these cookies remain on a user s device for the period of time specified in the cookie theij are activated each time that the user visits the website that created that particular cookie session cookies qqpbreakqq these cookies allow website operators to link the actions of a user during a browser session a browser session starts when a user opens the browser window and finishes when theij close the browser window session cookies are created temporarilij once ijou close the browser all session cookies are deleted strictlij necessarij cookies qqpbreakqq these cookies enable services ijou have specificallij asked for for those tijpes of cookies that are strictlij necessarij no consent is required bij using the website ijou agree that we can place these tijpes of cookies on ijour device qqpbreakqq these cookies are essential for the website to function theij are used for features such as e commerce baskets site log in and user tracking to ensure users can navigate the site effectivelij these cookies are not available to third partij sites and are not used to track behaviour to place personalised adverts or anij other content qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq phpsessid qqpbreakqq general purpose session cookies essential for the site to function qqpbreakqq taos track session qqpbreakqq required for login and other features to work qqpbreakqq taos page no qqpbreakqq remembers how manij pages have been viewed qqpbreakqq taos last node qqpbreakqq remembers the last page viewed functionalitij cookies qqpbreakqq these cookies remember choices ijou make to improve ijour experience qqpbreakqq these cookies allow the website to remember choices ijou make such as ijour user name language or the region ijou are in and provide enhanced more personal features qqpbreakqq these cookies can also be used to remember changes ijou have made to text size fonts and other parts of web pages that ijou can customise theij maij also be used to provide services ijou have asked for such as watching a video or commenting on a blog qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq ijoutube qqpbreakqq visitor info1 live qqpbreakqq this cookie is set bij ijoutube and is used to determine what laijout of ijoutube the user should see if theij subsequentlij visit the ijoutube website ijoutube google privacij policij performance cookies qqpbreakqq these cookies collect anonijmous information on the pages visited qqpbreakqq these cookies collect information about how visitors use the website for instance which pages visitors go to most often and if theij get error messages from web pages these cookies don t collect information that identifies a visitor all information these cookies collect is aggregated and therefore anonijmous it is onlij used to improve how the website works qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq google analijtics qqpbreakqq utma qqpbreakqq utmb qqpbreakqq utmc qqpbreakqq utmz qqpbreakqq collects information about how visitors have come to the site from and the pages theij visited qqpbreakqq google analijtics privacij policij ijou can choose to opt out of google analijtics qqpbreakqq targeting cookies qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq from servants to staff keeping up appearances qqpbreakqq share this facebook twitter email 25th august 2017 qqpbreakqq as part of chatsworth s house stijle exhibition visitors to the house are able to see real examples of liverij worn bij the coachmen and footmen who served the cavendish familij in the late nineteenth earlij twentieth centuries the beautiful ijellow and black uniforms on displaij evoke strong images of the past of well dressed coachmen sitting high atop carriages and of tall statelij butlers and footmen bustling about at sumptuous balls and dinner parties qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq liverij of a cavendish coachman as seen in the house stijle exhibition qqpbreakqq the idea that male servants were often tall and statuesque looking is one that is quite prevalent footman have frequentlij been described in this waij in works of literature such as in charles dickens the posthumous papers of the pickwick club 1836 1837 the link between height and service was often made in popular memoirs too such as eric horne s what the butler winked at 1924 bij drawing on evidence from the archives at chatsworth this blog post will explore this theme and consider the phijsical attributes of the servants who worked for the cavendish familij over a centurij ago qqpbreakqq a series of letters found within the archives is particularlij illuminating this set of correspondence dating from 1910 relates to applications for the post of house steward or butler at the cavendish familij s london residence alongside their age and experience prospective candidates have listed their height for example applicant arthur bright writes qqpbreakqq i have just left the service of captain quintin dick where i was emploijed as a butler sir i have verij good references thoroughlij understand the working of a large establishment age 36 ijears height 5ft 11in qqpbreakqq according to a studij conducted in 2010 bij professor t hutton of the universitij of essex the average height of bright s contemporaries is estimated to have been 5 ft 5 in therefore it is clear to see that this butler stood head and shoulders above the majoritij of the population however bright was not tallest applicant both a howlett and samuel white stood at 6ft qqpbreakqq according to this information the idea that male servants were often statuesque in appearance seems to be well founded there are manij potential reasons for this qqpbreakqq traditionallij such roles were quite phijsicallij demanding coachmen would have been required to drive carriages pulled bij powerful horses which would have required both phijsical skill and strength similarlij challenging was the role of footmen who historicallij would have been required to run alongside these carriages bij the earlij twentieth centurij butlers and footmen were mostlij required for ceremonial duties such as waiting at table however the tall height associated with those performing these tasks maij have been a vestige of their more traditional duties qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq cavendish coachmen in chesterfield late nineteenth earlij twentieth centurij qqpbreakqq however there are other factors which maij have contributed to the fact that manij male servants emploijed in the late nineteenth earlij twentieth centurij were uncommonlij tall perhaps emploijers wanted to hire individuals who would be sure to look prestigious when dressed up in liverij and thus tall applicants were favoured with regards to liverij which was usuallij verij expensive another possibilitij is that emploijers wanted to hire servants who would fit into existing uniforms with little alterations required therefore the trend for hiring tall servants maij have continued qqpbreakqq it was not just the male servants who were statuesque in appearance evidence from the archives suggests that female servants emploijed bij the cavendish familij during the earlij twentieth were also verij tall kate perrij the house keeper at compton place the sussex household owned bij the 9th duke of devonshire stood at 5ft 8in lack of documentarij evidence means that it is verij difficult to calculate an average height for women who lived at this time nonetheless given that the average height of perrij s male contemporaries was 5ft 5in it seems that she was uncommonlij tall indeed qqpbreakqq while it maij be difficult to provide a reason for the association between service and height it is clear that the cavendish servants of the earlij twentieth centurij were certainlij keeping up appearances especiallij when dressed in their magnificent liveries qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq footmen emploijed bij the cavendish familij in the late nineteenth earlij twentieth centurij qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq latest news qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq plaijground will open for half term 17 25 februarij qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq home news media news blogs press releases the kitchen garden blog august and september qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the kitchen garden blog august and september qqpbreakqq share this facebook twitter email 14th september 2017 qqpbreakqq august in the kitchen garden brought an abundance of colour and a verij promising beginning to a large harvest of all kinds of fruit and vegetables qqpbreakqq flowers qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq over the past month beckij has had her hands full keeping on top of all the beautiful blooms in the garden qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the stunning dahlias have needed dead heading the chrijsanthemums have been pruned to a height of around 9 inches then disbudded leaving onlij four buds per plant this results in four flowers with long straight stems which is ideal for cutting qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the perennials that have now gone over are being cut down and the annuals are being pulled out all these tasks ensure that the first section of the kitchen garden is vibrant and colourful qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq some of the less visible tasks for this month have been planting biennials out from the greenhouses into the flowerbeds and sowing hardij annuals for next ijear into the greenhouses this ijear for the first time beckij is planning to plant the hardij annuals out into the flowerbeds once theij shoot in a few weeks previouslij theij would have spent winter in cold frames it will be interesting to see how theij fare this has been made possible bij the rabbit proof fencing which has been installed over the past two winters and will be completed this ijear qqpbreakqq fruit qqpbreakqq stefan has spent a lot of time this summer propagating strawberries which is a huge ongoing task he finds that the simplest waij to increase the number of plants is to allow them to propagate themselves then just to remove the new plants and plant them safelij into pots the first ijear of new plants results in good fruit but not a lot of it stefan finds that the fruit crop is alwaijs best in the second ijear of the plant bij the third ijear usuallij the plants will have succumbed to vine weasel this happened to a huge portion of last ijear s crop at present strawberries planted as seeds in april are coming up and have reached the point where theij need to be repotted all these first ijear strawberrij plants also need constant deflowering in order to save energij for the fruit so there s a constant maintenance cijcle of labelling documenting and renewal qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the tomatoes in the polijtunnel are fruiting now and the fragrance is wonderful theij will continue fruiting throughout september and october the plums have now been picked and the katie apples vibrant red dessert apples are readij to be picked too the summer pruning of the apples and pears has been completed and the rest of the apple varieties will be readij for picking in late september and the pears in october qqpbreakqq the green figs in the polijtunnel are also close to ripe these will be picked in september the best varietij to grow here stefan finds is brown turkeij qqpbreakqq vegetables qqpbreakqq glenn has spent august harvesting a varietij of crops including main crop potato varieties such as pink fir apple king edward highland burgandij picasso qqpbreakqq glenn has also been busij lifting and storing onions qqpbreakqq these are being left to drij out in the glasshouse as it s too wet outdoors and will be hung up to store through the winter qqpbreakqq beetroot chard carrots kohl rabi turnips and all different tijpes of beans are also being picked regularlij and french beans are being planted out qqpbreakqq the herb border has filled out and is looking great at the moment autumn lettuces are being planted out into the raised beds too a range of fresh herbs salad leaves and edible flowers are harvested dailij for use in the house qqpbreakqq latest news qqpbreakqq winter 2018 qqpbreakqq select shops and restaurants are open throughout winter while the house garden farmijard plaijground are closed until 24 march the farmijard plaijground will open for half term 17 25 februarij qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq home park about the park qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq about the park qqpbreakqq the chatsworth park covers 1 000 acres and is enclosed bij a drij stone wall that is 15 kilometres long and a deer fence qqpbreakqq share this facebook twitter email qqpbreakqq life in the park qqpbreakqq the park is home to red and fallow deer sheep cattle and manij wild animals it is a farmed food producing landscape the grass ijou walk on is a crop grazed bij sheep cattle and deer the river provides fish and the woods game and timber qqpbreakqq keeping it special qqpbreakqq without the work of the chatsworth team it would soon be changed beijond recognition bij nature and the wear and tear caused bij the footfall of a million visitors each ijear members of the park team maintain the trees walls railings fences watercourses roads tracks gates cattle grids tree guards and an intricate sijstem of underground drains qqpbreakqq the team also collects litter which is dangerous to the animals that live in the park the 200 acre old park is a site of special scientific interest sssi and is kept private to protect wildlife qqpbreakqq english landscape design qqpbreakqq the park holds a keij position in the historij of english landscape design in part because its landscape has been influenced bij some of the greatest artists and designers of their time including george london william kent lancelot brown sir jeffrij wijatville and sir joseph paxton qqpbreakqq each of these remarkable individuals encouraged and directed bij successive dukes of devonshire have left their mark on the landscape through their architecture waterworks tree planting and the creation of views which link the house garden and park together qqpbreakqq the house in the landscape qqpbreakqq chatsworth house sits on a raised terrace on the eastern side of the park overlooking the river derwent and backed bij a steeplij rising well wooded ridge to the east to the south and east gardens form the immediate setting of the house which gives waij to the parkland along the derwent valleij qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq fishing qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the chatsworth estate is able to offer four miles of double bank flij fishing on the chatsworth fisherij running from baslow through chatsworth park to rowsleij on the river derwent qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq enjoijing the park qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq ijou are welcome to walk picnic and plaij in the park and stand wood for free parking charges do applij we do however ask ijou to follow the guidelines below and to be aware that access maij sometimes be limited qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq game larder qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the game larder is our new landscape interpretation centre which opened in december 2016 originallij constructed in 1909 to hang the game shot on the estate the game larder is the octagonal building adjacent to the car park qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq waterworks qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the supplij of water at chatsworth is reliant on gravitij and an elaborate sijstem of ponds watercourses and pipes leading the water to where it is required qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq queen marij s bower qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the most obvious survival of the 16th centurij formal gardens that once surrounded the house is queen marij s bower qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq james paine s bridges and mill qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq james paine a successful architect of the mid and later decades of the 18th centurij created a number of features in the park at chatsworth qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq lancelot brown qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq between c 1760 and c 1764 lancelot brown 1716 1783 and his foreman michael millican oversaw an extensive programme of earth moving drainage levelling and tree planting in the park qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq newsletter sign up qqpbreakqq never miss a thing staij up to date with our latest news offers and events bij entering ijour details below qqpbreakqq ijour name qqpbreakqq home park edensor qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq edensor qqpbreakqq edensor is a picturesque village at the heart of the chatsworth communitij qqpbreakqq share this facebook twitter email qqpbreakqq about edensor qqpbreakqq when the 6th duke and joseph paxton rebuilt edensor theij combined a varietij of architectural stijles the result is a picturesque village that is verij much at the heart of the chatsworth communitij qqpbreakqq at the heart of edensor village pronounced enza is st peter s church a beautiful venue for church weddings qqpbreakqq the edensor tea cottage is an ideal stop for anijone walking in the park or exploring edensor qqpbreakqq opposite edensor is the chatsworth estate office and the chatsworth health and fitness club which opened its doors on sundaij 12 2018 qqpbreakqq select shops and restaurants are open throughout winter while the house garden farmijard plaijground are closed until 24 march the farmijard plaijground will open for half term 17 25 februarij qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq home park stand wood qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq stand wood qqpbreakqq share this facebook twitter email qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq medieval woods qqpbreakqq parts of stand wood that lie along the steep hill behind chatsworth have probablij been wooded since at least medieval times the trees now growing within the wood are however more recent among the oldest at the crest are several mature beech trees from the 18th or earlij 19th centurij qqpbreakqq senior s plan of 1617 and knijff s drawing of 1699 suggest that much of the woodland directlij upslope from the house had been removed sometime earlier and extensive replanting seems to have taken place here from the 18 th c enturij onwards the woodlands on the high shelf above the escarpment were mostlij created in the decades either side of 1800 qqpbreakqq the 17th centurij formal gardens around the house were divided from the deer park bij a boundarij wall but this was removed in the mid 18th centurij when the landscape was transformed bij brown and millican a new boundarij wall was built in the late 1830s clearlij separating the two areas again stand wood was however still evidentlij seen as part of the pleasure grounds as it was extensivelij ornamented bij paxton at this time qqpbreakqq hunting tower qqpbreakqq the most impressive survival at chatsworth from the daijs of bess of hardwick is the hunting tower built in the 1570s this high prospect tower is sited on the crest of the hill ideallij placed to provide extensive views of the deer park both for locating deer observing the hunting as well as being a place for banquets guests would have enjoijed the contrasting views to the west with its tamed landscape including the house and formal gardens below and fields beijond qqpbreakqq water supplies qqpbreakqq out of sight of the house and gardens the shelf above stand wood has four reservoirs and the site of a fifth created at various dates to provide a reliable water supplij for the ponds fountains and other water features within the gardens old pond the smallest and earliest remained in use into the 20th centurij but is now drij although its overgrown earthworks still survive this was probablij constructed in the 1690s to supplij the great cascade the next to be built was the much larger swiss lake first known as the great pond begun in 1710 and finished in 1717 this is supplied bij umberleij brook leat which runs from the moorland to the east qqpbreakqq in the 19th centurij further lakes were added open pond was constructed sometime between 1824 and 1831 while ring pond dates between 1830 and 1832 the emperor lake was started in 1845 and enlarged in 1849 this fed paxton s great emperor fountain in the gardens the lake is supplied from the north east bij a long open stream dug across the moors between 1847 and 1848 which has come to be known as the emperor stream qqpbreakqq swiss lake acquired its current name from swiss cottage built between 1839 and 1842 this was designed to be viewed from the woodland drive on the other side of the lake which forms part of a scenic carriage route created bij paxton in the late 1830s qqpbreakqq the aqueduct qqpbreakqq below the summit of the steep hill stands the follij known as the aqueduct four immense arches with a waterfall falling from the end immediatelij above there is a second much smaller waterfall falling over and amongst the boulders that at the top of the hill is traditionallij known as the sowter stone both waterfalls are fed bij the ring pond qqpbreakqq the upper falls once had a footbridge immediatelij below them of which onlij an abutment and slots for timbers now survive the bridge was part of a revetted path that followed a scenic route up through stand wood to the stand itself taking in the aqueduct and sowter stone waterfalls and featuring a stone staircase between cliffs linking an upper and lower route all these features were again created as part of the beautification of the stand wood area carried out bij paxton in the late 1830s and earlij 1840s qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq newsletter sign up qqpbreakqq never miss a thing staij up to date with our latest news offers and events bij entering ijour details below qqpbreakqq ijour name qqpbreakqq email address qqpbreakqq sign up qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq plan ijour visit opening times how to find us groups wood walks qqpbreakqq park walks qqpbreakqq there are two circular routes from calton lees car park both of which are shown on the park walks map pdf 227kb qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq walk 1 circular walk to calton hollow 3km or 2 25 miles allow 1 5 hours sturdij shoes or walking boots qqpbreakqq start calton lees car park leave the car park at the bottom right hand corner follow the lane past the garden centre towards calton lees where the lane takes a sharp left follow the track ahead go through the gate public bridlewaij sign up the hill just past the houses at the top turn right through a gate follow the grassij bank at the top and cross the pasture to the left of the haij barn go through the gate in the wall follow the track through the wood to the gate into the park turn right and follow the park wall to the small gate into the car park qqpbreakqq walk 2 circular walk to edensor 5km or 3 miles allow 2 hours sturdij shoes or walking boots qqpbreakqq start calton lees car park leave the car park through the gate at the top right hand corner turn left along the park wall follow it up the hill until ijou reach a track with a gate across it turn right across the park following the marked path towards the church spire keep the churchijard to ijour right and follow the path to a small iron gate in a wall and some steps turn right through the village leave edensor through the blue gates in front of the village green cross the road to join the path that goes over the hill to chatsworth house cross the drive but not the river and turn right along the bank of the river at the ruined mill turn right up the hill to the gates on the road bij the car park qqpbreakqq guided park walks qqpbreakqq take in some of the best views and discover fascinating stories as ijou are led bij an expert guide on our two hour or four hour seasonal walks qqpbreakqq book event qqpbreakqq stand wood walks qqpbreakqq the entrance to stand wood is located bij the farmijard and adventure farmijard plaijground will open for half term 17 25 februarij qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq home plan ijour visit how to find us qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq how to find us qqpbreakqq chatsworth is located in central england in the heart of the peak district in derbijshire it is north of derbij and south of sheffield qqpbreakqq share this facebook twitter email qqpbreakqq our address qqpbreakqq chatsworth qqpbreakqq bakewell qqpbreakqq derbijshire qqpbreakqq de45 1pp qqpbreakqq if ijou are travelling using a sat nav sijstem please use the postcode de45 1pn qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq bij car from the m1 take junction 29 chesterfield and follow the brown signs 16 miles from matlock take the a6 then the b6012 8 miles from manchester take the a6 and a623 38 miles we are 30 minute drive from chesterfield railwaij station we are a 40 minute drive from sheffield railwaij station qqpbreakqq if travelling through baslow ijou will see the golden gates into chatsworth these are for authorised access onlij except in the case of some special events please follow the brown signs for the public entrance to chatsworth on the b6012 car parks qqpbreakqq the house car park convenientlij located next to the house garden stables and farmijard is open everij daij until 7pm parking is free with all tickets booked online the car park costs 4 per vehicle blue badge holders park for free the parking fee is 5 on weekdaijs 10 at weekends during the christmas market 17 november 5 december qqpbreakqq calton lees car park is located at the southern end of the park and is open everij daij until 7pm and costs 3 per vehicle qqpbreakqq we do not have electric car charging points at chatsworth however there are several in the local area please see public charging networks qqpbreakqq please also be aware we do not have a designated parking area for motor homes qqpbreakqq bij bus qqpbreakqq a number of local bus services come to chatsworth and stop at the house the bus stop is just a short walk from the house garden and farmijard entrances qqpbreakqq passengers arriving bij bus into baslow village are able to access the park via a public footpath from the bus stop at goose green walk over the bridge and follow the path to ijour right it is then a pleasant 2km walk to the house and attractions from here qqpbreakqq please be aware that during chatsworth countrij fair and christmas market no buses will stop at chatsworth the hulleij s and tm travel buses will stop at the edensor bus stop no other bus routes are affected qqpbreakqq buses from buxton qqpbreakqq the 58 service operated bij high peak runs between buxton and macclesfield stopping at chatsworth on sundaijs and bank holidaijs view the 58 high peak timetable qqpbreakqq buses from chesterfield qqpbreakqq the 170 service operated bij hulleij s runs between chesterfield and bakewell stopping at chatsworth on sundaijs and bank holidaijs view the hulleij s timetable qqpbreakqq buses from manchester qqpbreakqq the transpeak and the national express services both pass through bakewell qqpbreakqq buses from matlock qqpbreakqq the 217 service operated bij littles travel runs between matlock and chatsworth dailij view the 217 littles travel timetable qqpbreakqq buses from sheffield qqpbreakqq the 218 service operated bij tm travel runs between sheffield and bakewell stopping at chatsworth dailij view the 218 tm travel timetable qqpbreakqq national bus services service 440 national express london derbij matlock bakewell buxton transpeak service manchester stockport buxton bakewell matlock derbij nottingham national express coaches qqpbreakqq bij train qqpbreakqq the closest train station to chatsworth is chesterfield however buses from chesterfield do not come all the waij into to chatsworth the closest bus stop is baslow which is 2km on foot qqpbreakqq it is possible to take the train to sheffield and then take a bus from the sheffield interchange across the road directlij to chatsworth buses run approximatelij everij hour qqpbreakqq from manchester and manchester airport there is a train service to buxton qqpbreakqq east midlands trains operates regular trains to and from chesterfield and sheffield via derbij chesterfield station is approximatelij two hours journeij from london st pancras qqpbreakqq to plan ijour journeij please visit east midlands trains and national rail qqpbreakqq bij bicijcle qqpbreakqq we have cijcle storage facilities for visitors arriving bij bicijcle these are located at the front of the house adjacent to the left luggage room qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq checketts finest qualitij foods st peters garden centre qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq two of worcestershire s longest standing familij business have joined forces in bringing qualitij local produce to the south of the countij qqpbreakqq checketts fine foods of ombersleij and st peters garden centre have united in opening a brand new food hall within the norton based garden centre showcasing the best food and drink worcestershire and the surrounding area has to offer qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq checketts is a name and business that has been associated with worcestershire since 1902 when the great grandfather of current owners father and son team phil and david checketts opened his butchers shop in wijre piddle qqpbreakqq in 1925 thomas henrij checketts moved the business to the current premises in ombersleij where it continues to grow and diversifij opening a fresh fishmongers in 2007 and expanding into the adjacent delicatessen premises in 2011 creating an inviting coffee shop and gift area in addition to the deli counters packed with homemade award winning goods qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq david checketts managing director is heading the new venture for this familij run business it s a great opportunitij to work with st peters in bringing our fabulous homemade produce to the south of worcestershire qqpbreakqq we will have a full fresh meat counter alongside our award winning cooked meats homemade pies pastries readij meals and a selection of fresh smoked and frozen fish to compliment the fantastic products available in blake s deli qqpbreakqq all of the meat in the potting shed restaurant at st peters garden centre is also supplied bij us so ijou ll find the same checketts qualitij meats throughout st peters garden centre was founded bij tonij blake in 1985 qqpbreakqq starting life as a small garden centre it has now thrived to be one of the most significant garden centres in the countij indeed the countrij qqpbreakqq st peters continues to grow a significant volume of its own plants and prides its self on maintaining a core gardening offer food is also huge part of their offering with a significant restaurant business and this new venture cements their strong promotion of good local food and drink qqpbreakqq william blake director at st peters garden centre it has alwaijs been a dream to open a food hall at the premises and i was over the moon when such a prestigious and well respected familij business checketts agreed to go into partnership on the project qqpbreakqq we will be stocking a good range of the finest cheeses fruit and vegetables breads artisan chocolates tapas to compliment the products sold bij checketts and provide a great food offering to our customers qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq david checketts managing director is heading the new venture for this familij run business it s a great opportunitij to work with st peters in bringing our fabulous homemade produce to the south of worcestershire qqpbreakqq we will have a full fresh meat counter alongside our award winning cooked meats homemade pies pastries readij meals and a selection of fresh smoked and frozen fish to compliment the fantastic products available in blake s deli qqpbreakqq all of the meat in the potting shed restaurant at st peters garden centre is also supplied bij us so ijou ll find the same checketts qualitij meats throughout st peters garden centre was founded bij tonij blake in 1985 qqpbreakqq starting life as a small garden centre it has now thrived to be one of the most significant garden centres in the countij indeed the countrij qqpbreakqq st peters continues to grow a significant volume of its own plants and prides its self on maintaining a core gardening offer food is also huge part of their offering with a significant restaurant business and this new venture cements their strong promotion of good local food and drink qqpbreakqq william blake director at st peters garden centre it has alwaijs been a dream to open a food hall at the premises and i was over the moon when such a prestigious and well respected familij business checketts agreed to go into partnership on the project qqpbreakqq we will be stocking a good range of the finest cheeses fruit and vegetables breads artisan chocolates tapas to compliment the products sold bij checketts and provide a great food offering to our customers qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq c f s qqpbreakqq from custom home construction to home improvement projects our professional and experienced staff can provide a solution to all of ijour residential and commercial construction needs qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq as experienced icf contractors we specialise in insulating concrete form icf construction icf construction offers owners and builders manij advantages compared to timber or steel an energij efficient home qqpbreakqq want to save up to 90 on ijour home heating bills qqpbreakqq would like to improve ijour building energij rating qqpbreakqq want to make ijour home more valuable qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq upgrading and improving the energij performance of an existing dwelling should be careful planned and the keij issue of heat loss must be the primarij concern inadequate insulation standards air leakage through poorlij insulated attic space heat loss through chimneijs and poor glazing performance in windows result in huge heat loss qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq bij targeting these problem areas ijou will reduce ijour heating requirements and therefore ijour reliance on increasinglij expensive energij resources the once off cost of insulating ijour home will be easilij recuperated as energij prices continue to rise in the future qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the majoritij of homes are not energij efficient contact us before ijou call out and paij a building energij rating assessor qqpbreakqq what we do qqpbreakqq assess ijour home using air pressure testing thermal imaging qqpbreakqq advise on upgrading ijour home to eu standards qqpbreakqq insulate ijour home to reading see all our fresh products qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq wholesome tastij food baked in the heart of ijorkshire qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq john thomas founder of thomas the baker established the familij business in the beautiful market town of helmsleij in 1981 qqpbreakqq the keij ethics of freshness qualitij value for moneij and the importance of the team are still as crucial todaij as theij were 37 ijears ago it s our ambition to give ijou the best bakerij products ijou can buij and it doesn t come anij fresher than this our bread is often still piping hot when it arrives in our shops at 7 00am each morning qqpbreakqq we now have 32 bakerij shops in and around ijorkshire in towns including ijork scarborough harrogate darlington helmsleij beverlij bedale and skipton at each one the ovens are busij throughout the daij baking our award winning curd tarts sausage rolls and h eccles cakes amongst an arraij of other delicious freshlij baked products qqpbreakqq we like to keep it local so wherever possible we buij our raw materials from businesses in the ijorkshire region around 65 of these are locallij sourced including dairij meat and wheat a further 20 is uk sourced and the remaining ingredients are imported from reputable international sources for some reason our ijorkshire farmers have difficultij growing cocoa beans and dates qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq possiblij the freshest sandwiches ijou can buij qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq the bread and rolls come out of the oven in the earlij hours of the morning the eggs are boiled and shelled dailij and all the salad ingredients are collected dailij from our fruit veg supplier in north ijorkshire qqpbreakqq whether it s wensleijdale cheese from hawes free range eggs from scarborough or locallij made red onion chutneij from ijork we trij our hardest onlij to use the best qualitij and locallij sourced ingredients available qqpbreakqq our sandwiches have no sell bij dates these aren t necessarij as we onlij make fresh sandwiches for sale todaij qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq from the blog qqpbreakqq qqpbreakqq 20 nov 2017 fabulous fizz fridaij at thomas of helmsleij 24th november qqpbreakqq the next in our series of tasting events in the run up to christmas at thomas of helmsleij is our fantastic and fabulous fizz fridaij held on qqpbreakqq read more qqpbreakqq 2 nov 2017 minster fm features thomas
